txt.en: 'Thank you again for the walk, [placeholder]. Maybe things are not quite so grim after all.'

'A walk is just the thing, [placeholder]. You can tell me about your adventures. There is nothing I like quite so much as a good adventure-story.\n\n'Real adventures somehow aren't the same, are they?'
Instance: Frodo's Burden

'I'm sure you're a perfectly respectable [placeholder], but I'd just as soon you left Mr. Frodo alone. I don't mean no offence, but Mr. Frodo's gotten himself into trouble with strange folk before, if you take my meaning.'
'There is something I need to do, but... I am afraid.'
'I am afraid for my friends. They love me too much to let me do this myself.'
Frodo is outside the Last Homely House, taking in the night air.\n\nGandalf the Grey asked you to walk with Frodo Baggins and to gauge his state-of-mind.
'I almost wish they didn't.'

Frodo's Burden
Gandalf the Grey has asked you to speak with Frodo Baggins about his troubles.
'I once wished I could have adventures, like Bilbo did!'
'My own adventure wasn't like Bilbo's at all.'
'It is so beautiful. It's nothing like the Shire, though.'
'I'm sorry. I am not very good company tonight, am I?'

'I've always said that a nice walk in the night air will do wonders to clear one's head, and it seems that I was right -- I feel much better now, [placeholder].

'I enjoyed our conversation. If I see you again, we'll have to have another.

'When I see you again, I mean.'
